wikipedia_page.main: William Champion Streatfeild (1 September 1865 – 15 February 1929) was the Anglican Bishop of Lewes for a brief period in the second quarter of the 20th century. He was a descendant of the historic Streatfeild family, the father of the novelist Noel Streatfeild, and appears as the beloved but over-saintly father of the heroine, Victoria, in her autobiographical novel A Vicarage Family.
